OL,3,C'Public health crisis' declared after
OL,4,C'shocking' HMO conditions
OL,6,FA "public health crisis" has been
OL,7,Fdeclared over "shocking" conditions in
OL,8,Fclose to 100 buildings that have been
OL,9,Fconverted into houses of multiple
OL,10,Foccupations (HMOs).
OL,12,FThe Mayor of Salford Paul Dennett said
OL,13,Fthat the inspections of 91 HMOs found
OL,14,Fthat 99% did not meet health and
OL,15,Fsafety standards.
OL,17,FTenants living in buildings with fire
OL,18,Fhazards alongside damp and mould were
OL,19,Fthe most common issues found by
OL,20,Fcouncil inspectors, as well as "excess
OL,21,Fcold" due to poor heating.
