OL,3,C'Public health crisis' declared after
OL,4,C'shocking' HMO conditions
OL,6,F"This is a public health crisis as far
OL,7,Fas I'm concerned, out of 91 properties
OL,8,F99 per cent of them failed, that is
OL,9,Fabsolutely scandalous."
OL,11,FCouncillor John Merry supported the
OL,12,Fproposal for a city-wide HMO licensing
OL,13,Fscheme, saying: "I just think if
OL,14,Fyou're a tenant you can sleep a little
OL,15,Fbit easier knowing that your property
OL,16,Fis covered by landlord licensing,
OL,17,Fbecause it means that the landlord
OL,18,Fcannot escape their responsibility,
OL,19,Fand we can actually do something about
OL,20,Fit."
